The evidence with the title 'Don't ask, don't tell - Wikipedia ' says "don't ask, don't tell" (dadt) was the official United States policy on military service by gays, bisexuals, and lesbians, instituted by the Clinton Administration on february 28, 1994, when Department Of Defense directive 1304.26 issued on december 21, 1993, took effect, lasting until september 20, 2011. The policy  ... 
